features: SYMMETRICAL SHAPE: No “right side up” silicone pacifier for babies are fuss-free and won’t need to be adjusted to sit properly in baby’s mouth and fits perfectly under nose for easy breathing.
SILICONE NIPPLE: The BPA-free silicone boy and girl pacifier has the signature MAM design, with silky SkinSoft material and a symmetrical shape that's ideal for jaw and teeth development.
VENTILATED & COMFORTABLE SHIELD: These cute pacifiers for babies have a curved shield with openings to keep baby comfortable, prevent moisture build-up, and allow baby’s skin to breathe.

body.description: The MAM Matte Original Pacifier was developed by leading pediatric dentists and developmental psychologists to provide maximum comfort and style for 16+ months babies.* MAM silicone pacifier feature an innovative nipple designed to promote healthy oral development so you can soothe your toddler with confidence. Our orthodontic pacifiers for breastfed babies have a built-in air channel that naturally flattens and extends when sucked, mimicking a human nipple during breastfeeding. Plus, all of MAM's breastfeed pacifier nipples feature life-like, SkinSoft textured silicone and a symmetrical nipple that fits perfectly in baby's mouth at any angle. With multiple baby boy pacifier and girl pacifiers shapes and shield sizes to pick from, MAM nipples are easily accepted by babies of all ages, with 94% nipple acceptance among babies tested.*Developed with the International Children's Medical Research Society. **Market research 2010-2020, tested with 1,572 babies

reviews.reviewText: Can't go wrong with MAMs! My sister's children preferred a different brand of bottle but my children LOVE MAMs. I do too. The glow-in-the-dark MAM pacifiers are a game changer- highly recommend those!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The best pacifiers!
reviews.reviewText: These are the only pacifiers my daughter will take. The glow-in-the-dark one is such a nice feature it helps so much at night when she wakes up without one in her mouth wanting it back. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Finally, a pacifier my baby will take
reviews.reviewText: Pros: My fussy baby finally accepted this style pacifier (enough said). Baby just didn’t like the Philips avent style from the hospital or several other styles we tried. The MAM just seems easier for him to keep in. The glow in the dark one is my favorite as we’re desperate to settle him at the end of the night and it’s easy to pop back in.Cons: “Variety” is not how I’d describe these as I had been looking for three distinct nipple shapes. I didn’t realize the only difference in these is the decorative grip and the images on the ones I received didn’t match what was ordered.I would recommend these for someone looking to try a different style than the philips that are provided at the hospital or for anyone having trouble getting baby to take a pacifier.
